# Admin feature hub (Prism)

Use this layout for **server-scoped admin areas** that have several screens (list / new / edit / reports), so the **left sidebar stays one item** and **in-feature navigation** lives in the main column.

## URL shape

- **Hub (GET only):** `/admin/server/{serverName}/{feature}` — overview, ingest URLs, links into sub-areas.
- **Sub-routes:** `{feature}/…` for lists, forms, map, logs — keep RESTful segments (`devices`, `zones`, `map`, …).

## Sidebar (`templates/admin/_server_sidebar.html.twig`)

- **One nav item** per product area (e.g. `Habits`, `GPS`), route **always the hub**.
- **`activeSection`:** use a **single key** for the whole area (e.g. `habits`, `tracking`) on hub **and** all sub-pages so the sidebar highlight matches Habits.

## In-page navigation

- **`templates/admin/{feature}/_subnav.html.twig`** — horizontal pills: **Overview** (hub) + each major subsection.
- Pass an explicit flag, e.g. `habitsSubnav: 'hub'|'users'|'goals'` or `trackingSubnav: 'hub'|'devices'|'zones'|'map'|'events'`.
- **Include the subnav** at the top of `server_main` on hub, list, form, and report templates.

## Hub template

- **`{feature}/hub.html.twig`:** title + short description; if account type missing, **amber callout** + link to Accounts tab (same copy style as Habits).
- If enabled: show **ingest/API base URL** when relevant; **card grid** linking to each subsection (not nested `<a>` inside `<a>` — use separate card links).

## List / form pages

- **Breadcrumb** in header: `Feature / subsection` (font-mono), linking hub → subsection.
- **Flashes** after subnav (success / error).

## Controller

- Dedicated `*AdminController` with class-level `#[Route('/admin/server/{serverName}/…')]` prefix; **`home` or empty route** renders the hub (do not redirect to the first list unless you intentionally skip the hub).

**Reference implementations:** `src/Controller/HabitsAdminController.php` + `templates/admin/habits/`; `src/Controller/TrackingAdminController.php` + `templates/admin/tracking/` (hub: `hub.html.twig`, subnav: `_subnav.html.twig`).
